        "text": "15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Sin-Offering for the people is offered ‘as the first’ i.e. in the same way as Aaron’s Sin-Offering; the blood is not brought into the tabernacle, and the sacrifice is wholly consumed. This treatment gives rise to the question of ",
